SIMPLE: syllidian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syllidian
<hw>Syl*lid"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From NL.
<ets>Syllis</ets>, the typical genus.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
one of numerous species of marine annelids of the family
<fam>Syllidae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Many of the species are phosphorescent; others are
remarkable for undergoing strobilation or fission and for their
polymorphism. The egg, in such species, develops into an asexual
individual. When mature, a number of its posterior segments gradually
develop into one or more sexual individuals which finally break away and
swim free in the sea. The males, females, and neuters usually differ
greatly in form and structure.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syllogism</ent>⟦br⟧
